TO have and to hold the same, unto and to the use of her said Majesty the Queen, her heirs and successors forever.

And we hereby agree to accept the several provisions, payments, and reserves of the said treaty signed at the Qu’Appelle Lakes as therein stated, and solemnly promise and engage to abide by, carry out, and fulﬁl all the stipulations, obligations, and conditions therein contained on the part of said Chiefs and Indians therein named to be observed and performed, and in all things to conform to the articles of the said treaty as if we our- selves and the bands which we represent had been originally contracting parties thereto, and had been present and attached our signatures to the said treaty.

In witness whereof Her Majesty’s Commissioners and the said Indian Chiefs have hereunto subscribed and set their hands at Qu’Appelle Lakes, this ninth day of September, in the year of Our Lord one thousand eight hundred and seventy-ﬁve.

(Signed) W. J. CHRISTIE, Indian Commissioner.
